Warning: Portions are HUGE. Share. No matter how hungry you think you are, you won't make a dent in your plate and will feel like a horrible, wasteful person. Ok - brunch. Yes! There's nothing like nursing a hangover with shrimp and grits, buttery biscuits, spicy gumbo, sweet beignets. Yaaaaaassss. Bring it. Service is top notch - they have a great system goin' on - coffee kept getting refilled, plates bussed... we even were seated pretty promptly (and of course, we had reservations).

Shrimp and grits... say less. They always have great service and a good vibe. Totally kid friendly and always so sweet to my family. Even let them help out and draw on the infamous chalk board... live music and bomb food and cool people. Just gotta know when to go to avoid them waits... or just know how the board actually works and not the line!

Despite the long lines it is a must go. I literally had everything on the menu as I am a regular there LOL and they were all extremely great. They simply know what they are doing. Highly recommended!!

Not going to lie, this area is super runned-down and pretty scary but we went pretty early so it wasn't too bad. It was pretty crowded but not what I expected for a restaurant with over 8000+ reviews. Make sure to sign your name on the blackboard that's on the right side. Service was great and quick. The restaurant is pretty small so I wouldn't recommend coming here with a big group or else you're going to wait a long ass time. Beignet Flight: I wished I got this dish after my meal since I do't like sweets before my savory but God! That crawfish beignet was orgasmic! The apple, chocolate, and plain beignet were pretty good as well. I would have just gotten the crawfish instead. Fried Chicken Eggs Benedict: They need to sell this more often and the fried chicken. The fried chicken was so crunchy with so much spice and flavor. I would have just ordered a bunch of fired chicken.

My friends and I visited this restaurant after their wedding ceremony at the city hall since it's only 6 minutes walk away. We arrived at around 1pm. The restaurant looked quite packed then. We were lucky that the five of us didn't really have to wait after we put our name on the board. Our server was attentive - she took our drink order right away and we got our drinks within 5 minutes. I had the special drink - blueberry and pomegranate mimosa. I like how refreshing it is but I really didnt really tasted that much alcohol in it. Two of us ordered shrimp and grits - I really enjoyed it. The grits were creamy and I love the tomato sauce. They put quite a lot of cheese in the grits, though I'm not used to it but it still tasted good. The shrimps are also well cooked. My husband got one of the sandwiches but he wasn't too satisfied since all he got was two pieces of burger buns with ground turkey stir fried in tomato sauce and a bunch of fries. I tried it and wasn't a fan either. The other friends got BFC and he seemed to be quite happy with the fried chicken. All in all, it's a French soul food style restaurant that's not that common in the city. The food was decent but I wouldn't wait for an hour or two just to dine here.

Obviously there is not much more that can be said about this amazing breakfast joint in San Fran but I'm going to continue anyway. First you have to walk in and put your own name their big chalkboard. Why?? Because they are SO stinking busy that they got smart and said "Do it your damn self." Think smarter, not harder, I like that! I believe we waited for a little over an hour. Is a small restaurant that everyone wants to go to and I thought that was pretty good considering it was 12 o'clock on a Saturday. After scoping their Yelp Page I knew I wanted their Crawfish Beignets . They did not disappoint. Covered in Creole seasoning and puffed up to 4 times the size of my fist, was stuffed with warm crawfish covered in cheese and super flavorful sauce. Than I decided to have something I have never tried before. Shrimp and Grits... I figured, what a better place to try it for the first time. Holy cow... So good. The only problem is that grits are so filling. But I will say it was creamy, the sauce on top was decadent, the shrimp was perfectly cooked. I'm not sure I can try shrimp and grits anywhere else ever again. I just have a feeling it wont measure up. I just love the concept of this place. I think its very different. French Comfort food? Who would have guessed!? So happy I decided to wait in that line and give this place a try.

This was the first time I've been to Brenda's and I think it'll be my last. I ordered the Eggs Benedict Fried Chicken with potatoes. Ill first review my eggs. The eggs were poached to a good consistency. The yolk was nice and soft. The hollandaise sauce was a bit tart for my liking and bland. The biscuit was fluffy, creamy, and delicious. I broke off some of the biscuit and dipped it in some of the house made jam and it was delectable! The fried chicken was seasoned well but I felt that there was a lingering oil flavor. It only covers the size of the biscuit so you aren't gettinf a lot. It also did taste kind of similar to mcdonald's mcchicken. Overall, the eggs benedict would get 3 stars. It wasn't amazing but it wasn't completely inedible. The biscuit was the savior. Lastly, the potatoes I had were very difficult to eat. It tasted like boiled potatoes mixed poorly with cajun spices. There was no flavor, absolutely none from the potatoes. Maybe one of the cooks forgot to season? The potatoes definitely need to be seasoned more appropriately and could probably use a mix of other textures...possibly try to pan fry them??? I was sad to leave all my potatoes uneaten. Overall, my meal is a 2.5 but Ill round up to be nice. Please season your food!!!

I came during the between lunch and dinner hours, so there was less of a selection, but it wasn't a problem. I ordered a butter biscuit, beignet flight, and Grillades and Grits. All of the food was phenomenal. The food exceeded my expectations, with the exception of the beignets. I've already tried the best beignets from New Orleans, and these ones were just fried dough in comparison, with not enough fluffiness. However it was still delicious; no one can mess up fried dough and sugar. The biscuits with butter totally blew me away, with both the portions and flakiness. Next time I will go for lunch and try the BFC with extra biscuits.

Run to Brenda's and write your name in chalk on the wall ASAP. I was being modest and let a few people beat me to the chalk wall when I should have been pushing people out of the way. Jk. Beignets, yesssss. I normally prefer sweet but the Crawfish was the best of all. The wait is long but it's worth it. TIP: No outside drinks allowed inside so chug your coffee before brunch.
